rComments: He was a really great professor.  You can tell how much he genuinely enjoys the subject he teaches. He cares for his students and is always available if you need help. I do think that his tests are on the difficult side but once you are familiar with his style of questions you understand how to study for them. Start your assignments early!
Most approachable prof I've ever had. Enthusiastic about what he does and extremely helpful. Relatively fair tests. Definitely one of the profs I'll always remember.
Easily one of my favourite profs at U of T. His knowledge, enthusiasm and dedication to the courses and to helping students is paramount.

This course is seriously hard and detailed! If you don't have to take it, don't! It is very interesting but takes a lot of time and memorization of various reactions for carbohydrates, peptides/amino acids, lipids and nucleic acids

This Proff. is extremly rude. He lowered the class average since everyone did well on the first test. Also, hes probably the wierdest proff in all of UofT. I urge people not to take his course. He is not fair at all when it comes to his test.

This is probably the hardest course in terms of work load.  You have to know all the metabolic pathways, mechanisms and know to solve bioenergetic problems using thermodynamic equations.  Over all, the prof is helpful and clear but you HAVE to study 3x harder in this course than you did in CHM243.
I think its good idea to visit his office hours, he helps alot!
Dr. Strautmanis is one of a kind.
